1. Multi-Stage Dockerfile (⭐ Important)

Technique batata hai jo real-world mein use hoti hai:

# ========== STAGE 1: BUILD ==========
FROM node:18-alpine AS builder

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

COPY . .
RUN npm run build

# ========== STAGE 2: PRODUCTION ==========
FROM nginx:alpine AS production

# Stage 1 se sirf build folder copy karo
COPY --from=builder /app/build /usr/share/nginx/html

# Nginx default port
EXPOSE 80

# Nginx start karo
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

2. Multi-stage ke fayde:

| Without Multi-stage                  | With Multi-stage           |
| ------------------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| Image size: 500MB+                   | Image size: 20-30MB        |
| Build tools included (security risk) | Sirf production files hain |
| Source code exposed                  | Source code nahi dikhta    |
| Slow deployment                      | Fast deployment            |
| More storage cost                    | Less storage cost          |


NOTE :- Production mein hamesha multi-stage Dockerfile use karo.
